definitions.definition: A branching treelike graphical representation of the phylogenetic relationships between organisms showing which taxa have branched from common ancestors .
A phylogenetic tree that is strictly the outcome of a cladistic analysis.

main_definition: ( taxonomy ) A branching treelike graphical representation of the phylogenetic relationships between organisms showing which taxa have branched from common ancestors .
secondary_definitions: ( phylogenetics ) A phylogenetic tree that is strictly the outcome of a cladistic analysis.
